###  https://plasma-mds.org/ontology/plasma-o/PLSMO_C0002
plsmo:PLSMO_C0002 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                  rdfs:subClassOf plsmo:PLSMO_C0026 ;
                  chmo:IAO_0000115 "A set of settings and parameters of a device or instrument."@en ;
                  rdfs:label "Configuration"@en .


###  https://plasma-mds.org/ontology/plasma-o/PLSMO_C0003
plsmo:PLSMO_C0003 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                  chmo:IAO_0000115 "A device is an object that is invented or constructed to serve a specific function."@en ;
                  rdfs:label "Device"@en .


###  https://plasma-mds.org/ontology/plasma-o/PLSMO_C0013
plsmo:PLSMO_C0013 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                  chmo:IAO_0000115 """Plasma diagnostic methods used to measure properties of a plasma. Examples: invasive probe methods, passive spectroscopy, active spectroscopy, etc.
Wikipedia: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plasma_diagnostics"""@en ;
                  rdfs:label "Diagnostic Method"@en .


###  https://plasma-mds.org/ontology/plasma-o/PLSMO_C0017
plsmo:PLSMO_C0017 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                  rdfs:subClassOf plsmo:PLSMO_C0034 ;
                  chmo:IAO_0000115 "A Qualitative Descriptor is a type of descriptor that describes an entity by expressing a quality, property, or feature in a non-numerical manner. It conveys information about the entity's characteristics, attributes, or nature using words, terms, or concepts rather than measurements or numbers. Example: thermal, virucidal, high-frequency, etc."@en ;
                  rdfs:label "Qualitative Descriptor"@en .


###  https://plasma-mds.org/ontology/plasma-o/PLSMO_C0021
plsmo:PLSMO_C0021 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                  rdfs:subClassOf plsmo:PLSMO_C0030 ;
                  chmo:IAO_0000115 """A scientific experiment is a research method which permits the investigation of cause-effect relations between known and unknown (target) variables of the field of study (domain). An experimental result cannot be known with certainty in advance.

EXPO ontology: http://www.hozo.jp/owl/EXPOApr19.xml/ScientificExperiment"""@en ;
                  rdfs:label "Scientific Experiment"@en .


###  https://plasma-mds.org/ontology/plasma-o/PLSMO_C0026
plsmo:PLSMO_C0026 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                  chmo:IAO_0000115 "Description is an information about an object. For example, a device is an object that can have a specification, configuration, and/or properties. A description consists of both quantitative and qualitative descriptors. Such as physical quantities and some qualitative characteristics."@en ;
                  rdfs:label "Description"@en .


###  https://plasma-mds.org/ontology/plasma-o/PLSMO_C0030
plsmo:PLSMO_C0030 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                  chmo:IAO_0000115 "Any systematic investigation or inquiry aimed at increasing knowledge or understanding. This is a broad term that can include various research methods, including experiments, observational studies, surveys, etc."@en ;
                  rdfs:label "Research Activity"@en .


###  https://plasma-mds.org/ontology/plasma-o/PLSMO_C0034
plsmo:PLSMO_C0034 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                  chmo:IAO_0000115 "A Descriptor is an attribute or characteristic that provides information about an entity. It can be qualitative, expressing a quality or feature in a non-numerical manner (e.g. color, texture, behavior), or quantitative, expressing a measurable property with a numerical value and unit (e.g. frequency, mass, length)."@en ;
                  rdfs:label "Descriptor"@en .


###  https://qudt.org/schema/qudt/Unit
<https://qudt.org/schema/qudt/Unit> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                    chmo:IAO_0000115 """A unit of measure, or unit, is a particular quantity value that has been chosen as a scale for measuring other quantities the same kind (more generally of equivalent dimension). For example, the meter is a quantity of length that has been rigorously defined and standardized by the BIPM (International Board of Weights and Measures). Any measurement of the length can be expressed as a number multiplied by the unit meter. More formally, the value of a physical quantity Q with respect to a unit (U) is expressed as the scalar multiple of a real number (n) and U, as Q = nU
."""@en ;
                                    rdfs:label "Unit" .


#################################################################
#    Individuals
#################################################################

###  http://purl.allotrope.org/ontologies/result#AFR_0001089
AFO:AFR_0001089 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                         QUDT:QuantityKind ;
                chmo:IAO_0000115 "Retention time is a chromatography peak facet that indicates the elapsed time between the injection of the sample and the maximum detector response attributed to the peak (analyte band). [Allotrope]"@en ;
                dcterms:references AFO:AFR_0000413 ;
                rdfs:label "Retention Time"@en .


###  http://purl.allotrope.org/ontologies/result#AFR_0001250
AFO:AFR_0001250 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                         QUDT:QuantityKind ;
                chmo:IAO_0000115 "A detector sampling rate setting is a detector setting parameter that specifies the rate at which the detector changes its output signal. It is limited by the actual physical/chemical process of detection and the detector electronics. Often the sample rate is set lower than the maximum sampling rate so that adjacent data points can be averaged to provide better signal to noise. [Allotrope]"@en ;
                rdfs:label "Detector Sampling Rate Setting"@en .


###  http://purl.allotrope.org/ontologies/result#AFR_0001881
AFO:AFR_0001881 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                         QUDT:QuantityKind ;
                chmo:IAO_0000115 "Flow rate is a quality quantification facet that quantifies the motion of material through a surface per time. [Allotrope]"@en ;
                rdfs:label "Flow Rate"@en .


###  http://purl.allotrope.org/ontologies/result#AFR_0001948
AFO:AFR_0001948 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                         QUDT:QuantityKind ;
                chmo:IAO_0000115 "The retention time window width is the full width of a retention time window for a chromatographic peak. [PSI/MS]"@en ;
                rdfs:label "Retention Time Window Width"@en .


###  http://purl.allotrope.org/ontologies/result#AFR_0002030
AFO:AFR_0002030 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                         QUDT:QuantityKind ;
                chmo:IAO_0000115 "A column inner diameter (datum) is an inner diameter quantifies the inner diameter of a column. [Allotrope]"@en ;
                rdfs:label "Column Inner Diameter"@en .


###  http://purl.allotrope.org/ontologies/result#AFR_0002768
AFO:AFR_0002768 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                         QUDT:QuantityKind ;
                chmo:IAO_0000115 "A column void volume time is the time required for an unretained compound to traverse the column and exit. [Allotrope]"@en ;
                rdfs:label "Column Void Volume Time"@en .


###  http://qudt.org/vocab/quantitykind/Pressure
<http://qudt.org/vocab/quantitykind/Pressure> rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                       QUDT:QuantityKind ;
                                              chmo:IAO_0000115 "Pressure is an effect which occurs when a force is applied on a surface. Pressure is the amount of force acting on a unit area. Pressure is distinct from stress, as the former is the ratio of the component of force normal to a surface to the surface area. Stress is a tensor that relates the vector force to the vector area."@en ;
                                              rdfs:label "Pressure"@en .


###  http://qudt.org/vocab/quantitykind/Time
<http://qudt.org/vocab/quantitykind/Time> rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                   QUDT:QuantityKind ;
                                          chmo:IAO_0000115 "Time is a basic component of the measuring system used to sequence events, to compare the durations of events and the intervals between them, and to quantify the motions of objects."@en ;
                                          rdfs:label "Time"@en .


###  http://qudt.org/vocab/quantitykind/Wavelength
<http://qudt.org/vocab/quantitykind/Wavelength> rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                         QUDT:QuantityKind ;
                                                chmo:IAO_0000115 "For a monochromatic wave, \"wavelength\" is the distance between two successive points in a direction perpendicular to the wavefront where at a given instant the phase differs by 2π. The wavelength of a sinusoidal wave is the spatial period of the wave—the distance over which the wave's shape repeats. The SI unit of wavelength is the meter."@en ;
                                                rdfs:label "Wavelength"@en .


